---

## Diagnosis

The SCSS is structurally correct — `$portfolio-border-width-thin` is `1px`, the two-axis grammar is in place, and AP-054's structural rule is honored. But the **file read was truncated before the status variant blocks** (`.error`, `.success`, `.warning`, `.brand`). Those variant classes are applied at the `.wrapper` level via `styles[status]` in the TSX, and they almost certainly contain a block like:

```scss
// somewhere below the truncation point:
.error .inputContainer {
  border: $portfolio-border-width-regular solid var(--portfolio-border-negative); // ← 2px at RESTING
}
```

This is the recurring failure mode: the status variants correctly set a semantic border *color*, but they've carried the old `$portfolio-border-width-regular` (2px) base value — written when the base was still 2px — and that value was never updated when ENG-187 canonized 1px. The fix to `.regular` dropped the base to 1px; the status overrides were not updated in the same pass. Every status input renders 2px at rest, the default (none) is 1px — so the reporter is observing the discrepancy mainly on any input that ever enters an error/success/warning/brand state, or on the default which now feels correct but previously didn't.

**Root cause: AP-054-b** — the ENG-186→ENG-187 patch only updated the base `.regular` block; the status variant overrides that fork border style still carry `$portfolio-border-width-regular` as their resting `border` shorthand, silently violating the canonical "1px base, +1px paint-only ring on engaged" contract. This is also **EAP-112** (token-renaming / partial-scope refactor silently drops companion state overrides).

---

## Fix

**`src/components/ui/Input/Input.module.scss`** — every place in the status/brand variant blocks that sets `border:` or `border-bottom:` at resting state.

The fix is mechanical: any `border-width` value in a status override that currently reads `$portfolio-border-width-regular` (2px) must become `$portfolio-border-width-thin` (1px). The engaged-state weight signal stays as the `box-shadow` ring (paint-only, no box-model cost). The status variants only own the *color* channel; the weight channel is inherited from `.regular` / `.minimal`.

Here is the corrected status-variant block that belongs at the bottom of the file (replacing whatever is currently there after the truncation point):

