#### FB-225: "Fourth time reporting Input border thickness. Default is 2px now."

**UX Intent:** Resting input border must read as hairline (1px); engaged border
reads as heavier (visual 2px) via the paint-only box-shadow ring. The weight
channel communicates interaction affordance without layout jitter.

**Root Cause:** ENG-187 corrected `$portfolio-border-width-thin` (1px) in the
`.regular` base block but did not propagate the same correction to the four
status variant blocks (`.error`, `.success`, `.warning`, `.brand`). Those blocks
retained `$portfolio-border-width-regular` (2px) in their resting `border:`
shorthands — so any input with a status class rendered a 2px border at rest.
Anti-patterns: **AP-054-b** (partial-scope propagation of a border-width fix),
**EAP-112** (token-renaming/partial refactor silently drops companion overrides).

**Resolution:** All status variant blocks updated to use `$portfolio-border-width-thin`
for their resting `border:` / `border-bottom:` shorthand. Engaged-state ring
remains a `box-shadow` 1px overlay — same grammar, same color token per status.
The default (none) state was already correct; only status variants were broken.

**Pattern extracted → AP-054-b amendment: scope clarified to ALL emphasis × status
combinations, not just .regular/none.**
