---

## Principle

**AP-054-b + EAP-112 — partial-scope propagation.** Every iteration of this bug has the same shape: a fix is applied to the base/default combination and never propagated to the variant matrix. The canonical rule must be stated as a **matrix invariant**, not a base-case rule:

> `border-width` is **`$portfolio-border-width-thin` at every resting state, for every emphasis × status combination.** The weight channel is exclusively owned by `box-shadow`. Any block that sets `border:` or `border-bottom:` must use `$portfolio-border-width-thin` — no exceptions, no status variant may override the thickness upward at rest.

The comment block already present in `.regular` is correct — it now needs to appear verbatim at the top of every status variant block, not just in the base.
